{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17585162","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17585162"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T08:04:48+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T08:04:48+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14917"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14917","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14917"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.08,0,0.03,0.89,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7605"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115402"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7605","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7605"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14917"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97405"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4908"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"5440"},{"type":"tags","id":"8525"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18608"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18609"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115402","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/115402"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ET lymphocytes are crucial components of the adaptive immune system that undergo a complex maturation process before becoming functional immune cells.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following organs is the site where T lymphocytes complete their maturation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Spleen","Gall bladder","Liver","Thymus","Thyroid gland"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ethymus\u003C/strong\u003E is the correct answer as it is the primary lymphoid organ where T cells undergo maturation, including positive and negative selection processes to ensure proper immune function. The \u003Cstrong\u003Espleen\u003C/strong\u003E is a secondary lymphoid organ that filters blood and houses mature lymphocytes, but is not a site of T cell maturation. The \u003Cstrong\u003Egall bladder\u003C/strong\u003E has no immune function and is involved in bile storage. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eliver\u003C/strong\u003E contains immune cells but is not involved in T cell maturation. The \u003Cstrong\u003Ethyroid gland\u003C/strong\u003E is an endocrine organ with no direct role in immune cell development.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn the thymus, immature T cells (thymocytes) undergo several developmental stages including expression of T cell receptors, positive selection to ensure recognition of self-major histocompatibility complex molecules, negative selection to eliminate self-reactive T cells, and development into either CD4+ or CD8+ T cells.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["T lymphocytes complete their maturation process in the thymus gland","The thymus is a primary lymphoid organ essential for T cell development and selection","T cells undergo positive and negative selection in the thymus to ensure proper immune function"],"references":["Janeway CA Jr, Travers P, Walport M, et al. Immunobiology: The Immune System in Health and Disease. 5th edition. New York: Garland Science; 2001. Generation of lymphocytes in bone marrow and thymus. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK27123/","Playfair, J. H. L., \u0026 Chain, B. M. (2012). Immunology at a Glance. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Marshall JS, Warrington R, Watson W, Kim HL. An introduction to immunology and immunopathology. Allergy Asthma Clin Immunol. 2018 Sep 12;14(Suppl 2):49. doi: 10.1186/s13223-018-0278-1. PMID: 30263032; PMCID: PMC6156898."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97405"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14917"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97405","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/97405"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-23T15:32:15+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-23T15:32:26+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7605"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115402"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4908","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4908"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Immunology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-14T17:03:52+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-14T17:03:52+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"10"}},